race.comment: SIMPLY ROYALTY (6) won on debut at Northam before a sound run at Bunbury in a much tougher race prior to the spell. The mare resumes without a trial today for the Harding stable and she maps for a lovely run under Gaerth. Can return on a positive note. BUSTER'S GIRL (8) has trialled very nicely in readiness for this and showed good ability in her last campaign. With a new stable now, but she hasn't lost a yard and a bold effort is expected on resumption. ROYAL ACCOLADE (1) disappointed at the end of last campaign but was in very good touch at this course prior. Has the speed to cross from out wide if he wishes and if he can dictate from the front, he'll be hard to mow down. ULTIMATE PARADISE (5) rates highly off his form at the end of last campaign and has to be included on that form. LACIE ACE (9) can run a cheeky race first-up with no weight on her back.
